    <title>Create Scorecards using the Pivot Table app</title>
    <para><emphasis><emphasis role="bold">Scorecards definition:</emphasis> In public health
        settings such as Ministries of Health, scorecards offer a useful and standardized method for combining related indicators into one table. A scorecard gives an overall view of the performance of a health program such as a vaccination program, highlighting successes, weaknesses, and areas for improvement
            Here's what a typical  scorecard looks like:</emphasis>  
        <screenshot>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_pivot_result.png"
                        align="left" width="90%" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </screenshot></para>
    <para>This tutorial explains how to create a scorecard in the DHIS2 Pivot Table app. There are
        several advantages to using the Pivot Table to create a scorecard, such as:</para>
    <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>You can save the scorecard on the dashboard and use it offline.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>You can share the scorecard with other DHIS2 users.</para>
        </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    <para>Let's get started!</para>
    <section><title>Create a legend for your scorecard</title>
        <para>First, we’ll create a 3-color “traffic light” legend for the scorecard. With three
            basic colors, the scorecard is easy to scan and easy to understand.</para>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app. Click the menu in
                    the top right corner and select Maintenance from the list of apps. You can also
                    type the first letters of the word maintenance in the search field to find the app.<screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_maintenance_app.png"
                                    align="left" width="60%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the Maintenance app, scroll to the bottom of the page right down to the
                        <emphasis role="bold">Other</emphasis> section.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Go to <emphasis role="bold">Legend</emphasis> and click the <emphasis
                        role="bold">+</emphasis>.<screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_maintenance_legend.png"
                                    align="left" width="25%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Legend Management</emphasis> page, scroll to the
                    bottom of the page and create a new legend by clicking the blue + button.<screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_maintenance_addbtn.png"
                                    align="left" width="6%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Enter a name for the legend such as “Traffic light”, a start value and an end
                    value in the fields. The values you enter here depend on the performance ratings
                    you wish to set for the scorecard.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Change <emphasis role="bold">Number of legend items</emphasis> to 3 to display
                    three colors in the scorecard. To change the legend item colors, click the blue
                    + button and then edit the colors.<screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_maintenance_legend_color.png"
                                    align="left" width="70%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot></para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist></section>

    <section><title>Create a scorecard in the Pivot Table app</title>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Pivot Table</emphasis> app from the top right
                    menu of the dashboard. You can also enter the first letters of Pivot Table in
                    the search field.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Go to <emphasis role="bold">Data</emphasis> in the pane on the left side and
                    select <emphasis role="bold">Indicators</emphasis> in the list.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Select an <emphasis role="bold">Indicator group</emphasis> such as “ANC” in
                    the second list.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Using the arrows, select the type of indicators you want to see in your scorecard.<screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_pivot_indicators.png"
                                    align="left" width="60%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Update</emphasis>. This button is in the menu at
                    the top of the workspace</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Go to <emphasis role="bold">Periods</emphasis> and select a period for which
                    you want to display data. In this “traffic light” example, we’ll use the
                    relative period section. In <emphasis role="bold">Quarters</emphasis>, select
                        <emphasis role="bold">This quarter </emphasis>and <emphasis role="bold">Last
                        quarter</emphasis>. Clear any other checkboxes and click <emphasis
                        role="bold">Update</emphasis>.<screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_pivot_period.png"
                                    align="left" width="60%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Go to <emphasis role="bold">Organisation Units</emphasis> in the same left
                    side pane, and click the arrow next to the gear button.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Select <emphasis role="bold">Select levels</emphasis>.<screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_pivot_orgunit_level.png"
                                    align="left" width="60%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Select <emphasis role="bold">District</emphasis> from the list (next to the
                    gear button). Click <emphasis role="bold">Update</emphasis>.<screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_pivot_orgunit_level2.png"
                                    align="left" width="60%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot></para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist><para>As you can see, the scorecard is starting to take shape in the workspace. Now it’s time to fine-tune the look and feel.</para></section>

    <section><title>Organise the layout and display of your scorecard</title>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the workspace, click <emphasis role="bold">Layout</emphasis>. <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata
                                    fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_pivot_layout.png"
                                    align="left" width="60%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>In <emphasis role="bold">Table layout</emphasis>, drag <emphasis role="bold"
                        >Organisation units</emphasis> down to the <emphasis role="bold">Row
                        dimensions</emphasis> section.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Drag <emphasis role="bold">Data</emphasis> to the <emphasis role="bold">Column
                        dimensions</emphasis> section.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Column dimensions</emphasis> pane, drag <emphasis
                        role="bold">Periods</emphasis> below <emphasis role="bold">Data</emphasis>,
                    and click <emphasis role="bold">Update</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the workspace, click <emphasis role="bold">Options</emphasis>.<screenshot>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata
                                    fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_pivot_options.png"
                                    align="left" width="50%" format="PNG"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </screenshot></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Go to <emphasis role="bold">Data</emphasis> and clear all the
                    checkboxes.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Go to <emphasis role="bold">Style</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold">Legend
                        set</emphasis> and from the list, select the legend you created in the
                    Maintenance app. In this example, we called it Traffic light.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Go to <emphasis role="bold">Style</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold">Legend
                        display style</emphasis> and select <emphasis role="bold">Background
                            color</emphasis>. </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Update</emphasis>. </para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
        <para>The Scorecard is ready! </para><screenshot>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_pivot_result.png"
                        align="left" width="100%" format="PNG"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </screenshot></section>
    <section>
        <title>Save and share your Scorecard</title>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the workspace, go to the <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis>
                    menu.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Save as</emphasis>. Enter a name for your
                    Scorecard.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>To share your Scorecard, select <emphasis role="bold"
                    >Favorites</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Enter the name of a user group name, and click <emphasis role="bold"
                        >Save</emphasis>. Your scorecard can be viewed by people that you share a
                    dashboard with.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
 
    
</section>
